# Vector Memory Implementation Overview

This project involves adding optional long-term vector memory to `ask-llm`.
This uses `ChromaDB` and `sentence-transformers` for storage and retrieval of past conversation snippets.

The feature is controlled by the `--memory` flag handled in [src/ask_llm/cli.py](mdc:src/ask_llm/cli.py) and enabled within the main application logic in [src/ask_llm/core.py](mdc:src/ask_llm/core.py).

The core memory management happens in [src/ask_llm/memory.py](mdc:src/ask_llm/memory.py).

Configuration options related to memory (persistence path, embedding model) are defined in [src/ask_llm/utils/config.py](mdc:src/ask_llm/utils/config.py).
